        "content": "<p><span class=\"user-mention silent\" data-user-id=\"684366\">Edward van de Meent</span> <a href=\"#narrow/channel/239415-metaprogramming-.2F-tactics/topic/Collecting.20binders/near/509276482\">said</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>do you konw about <a href=\"https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathlib4_docs/Lean/Meta/Basic.html#Lean.Meta.lambdaTelescope\">Lean.Meta.lambdaTelescope</a>?</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>Yes, but in this case I may have both lambdas and foralls, and I wonder if there's a solution to this case. If its just lambda's or just forall's then its easy</p>",
